# Render Deployment Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the exact steps to transition your local project to a live production environment on Render. We will use a **Separated Architecture** (Backend as a Web Service, Frontend as a Static Site) which is the most reliable way to deploy React + Node apps on Render.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **MongoDB**: You MUST create a free account on [MongoDB Atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas) and get a connection string. Local MongoDB won't work on Render.
> - **Environment Variables**: You will need to manually copy each key from your `.env` file into the Render dashboard during setup.

